<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He married British singer Lily Allen In Las Vegas a week ago.</p>

<p>But on Monday, Stranger Things star David Harbour was all alone as he stepped out in New York City.</p>

<p>The actor, 45, was spotted grabbing a snack in Downtown Manhattan despite current COVID-19 regulations that require anyone returning from Nevada to New York to quarantine for 14 days. </p>

<p>Newlywed: He married British singer Lily Allen In Las Vegas a week ago. But on Monday, Stranger Things star David Harbour, 45, was all alone as he stepped out in New York City</p>

<p>The actor was dressed casually in a t-shirt and shorts and made sure to wear a face mask.</p>

<p>He enjoyed his  refreshments while seated alone at an outdoor table at the cafe and socially distanced from others. </p>

<p>Harbour and Allen obtained a marriage license in Vegas on Sunday September 6 and wed on Monday September 7 with an Elvis impersonator officiating.  </p>

<p>New York state law requires anyone arriving from a restricted state to remain in self-isolation and not go out in public for 14 days from arrival.</p>

<p>As of September 9, Nevada is listed as a restricted state on the New York government website.</p>

<p>The only exemption would be for someone who was passing through a restricted state and spent less than 24 hours there. </p>

<p>DailyMail.com has reached out to Harbour's representative for comment.  </p>

<p>Out and about: Harbour enjoyed a snack outdoors at a Manhattan cafe, despite COVID-19 rules in New York that state anyone coming from Nevada should quarantine for 14 days</p>

<p>Popular role: Harbour found fame as Jim Hopper, the chief of police of Hawkins, Indiana, in the Netflix blockbuster series Stranger Things. He's due to start work on season 4 soon</p>

<p>Harbour found fame as Jim Hopper, the chief of police of Hawkins, Indiana, in the Netflix blockbuster series Stranger Things.</p>

<p>The role earned him Emmy and Golden Globe nominations.</p>

<p>He and Allen, 35, were first linked in August 2019 when they were seen together at a theatre in London.</p>

<p>They divide their time between the UK and the US and sparked engagement rumors in May when Allen was seen with a sparkler on her ring finger in an Instagram post. </p>

<p>Said 'I do': Harbour and Allen tied the knot at the famous Graceland Wedding Chapel in Las Vegas on Monday September 7 after picking up a marriage license the day before</p>

<p>So happy: The British singer, 35, exchanged vows wearing a short 60s-inspired Dior dress with bateau neckline and veil. It's her second marriage and his first</p>

<p>Fun reception: : After the ceremony, the newlyweds enjoyed burger sand fries along with Allen's two daughters, Ethel, eight, and Marnie, seven</p>

<p>They tied the knot at the famous Graceland Wedding Chapel in Las Vegas accompanied by Allen's daughters from her first marriage - Ethel, eight, and Marnie, seven.</p>

<p>In snaps shared from the ceremony, Allen exchanged vows wearing a short 60s-inspired Dior dress with bateau neckline and veil.</p>

<p>The newlyweds celebrated their nuptials with burgers and fries from fast food chain In-N-Out.  </p>

<p>Sharing photos to his Instagram last week, Harbour wrote: 'In a wedding officiated by the king himself, the people's princess wed her devoted, low born, but kind credit card holder in a beautiful ceremony lit by the ashen skies courtesy of a burning state miles away in the midst of a global pandemic.'</p>

<p>Suited: The couple were first linked in August 2019 when they were seen together at a theatre in London. They divide their time between the UK and the US (pictured in January in LA)</p>
